      "writtenOn": "2020-12-14T16:31:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "There is some misunderstanding.\neventbox is only for Project manager because it must handle \u003e1 QPS of incoming events.\nPoller doesn\u0027t need it, it\u0027s \"poked\" at once per ~10 seconds.\n\nAre you asking why previously it was a SideEffectFn executed during PM transaction and now it\u0027s fine to do it before transaction? That\u0027s because poking poller doesn\u0027t need to be atomic with updating PM entity -- the new config is already stored in datastore.",
      "parentUuid": "432da6b4_d6ce0d10",
      "revId": "f0cf320aca57f9314231ce92ae72c157a092f758",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
